        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Influenced by is a mostly-different story; I don't like that the LLM-generated content exists, but there is no reason someone can't take inspiration from it and write their own version. There may end up being similarities, or even one those tiny patches where there is essentially only one way to make the necessary change. I can live with that; everything in life is a compromise.\n\nI think you're right about this needing a more direct interaction with upstream although it seems to be a moot point. I see at least six commits openly using LLM content with who knows how many that just don't admit it.\n\nI'm going to go ahead and close the issue; I appreciate the time you've taken (and all the work you've done on neovim!).",
