        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "This has nothing to do with code quality (which is anecdotally rather horrible); this is purely about the fact that they are unethical plagiarism machines.\n\nI know the United States has definitively stated (and had upheld by the courts) that anything output by an LLM(be it code, \"art\", a novel, etc.) cannot be copyrighted. If there are not other countries that have done so, it is likely to only be a matter of time.\n\nLLM usage is a hard line for an increasing number of people in the OSS community; I and thousands of others are intentionally discarding projects that incorporate this garbage. I hope y'alls will read the room and realize you need to stomp on this problem now, before it's too late. Two commits can be worked around; two hundred cannot. There are already people (myself included) who are working on getting different editors setup, or planning on staying on a pre-LLM release until we can do so, and this is over only those _two commits_.",
