        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Like @bfredl, I find your tone and wording highly problematic. As maintainers for a reasonably large open source project, we are obviously concerned with the effect of LLMs and coding agents on code quality and maintainer load and are discussing how to best handle it to ensure the health of the project. However, trying to shame or bully us into a blanket \"AI is poison!\" knee-jerk stance with lines like \n\n> LLM usage is a hard line for an increasing number of people in the OSS community; I and thousands of others are intentionally discarding projects that incorporate this garbage. \n\nis not a welcome contribution. Neovim is provided as-is and free of charge; if you don't want to use it, fine, but that's your problem, not ours. Maybe [icevim](https://github.com/icevim-editor/icevim/) will meet your standards. ",
            "created_at": "2026-03-07T10:05:57Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38186#issuecomment-4016156592",
