        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "According to what others have said, Vim does not ban the use of AI but requests\nthat it be disclosed (I didn’t know that). In other words, the developer in\nthis case responded honestly by admitting they used AI.\n\nWhat would happen if the use of AI were completely banned in Vim/Neovim development?\n\nMost likely developers would start hiding their use of AI. I can’t help but feel that would become a bigger problem down the line.\n\nI understand that there are concerns about using AI. However, the Vim/Neovim\nsource code is complex, and it is also true that some people are collaborating\nwith AI to help solve problems.",
